   SynapseGit repository or its Releases, excluding Third-Party Materials. It
   includes versions made available before or after the effective date,
   including v0.1.0, unless a version is accompanied by different license
   terms.

   "GitHub Service" means the repository hosting service at github.com.

   "GitHub Fork" means a public repository created from the official
   SynapseGit repository by using the GitHub Service's fork functionality and
   remaining within that repository network.

   "Production Use" means use with production data or to operate or support a
   live service, external deliverable, operational business or organizational
   process, or operational decision.

   "Hosted Service" means allowing a third party to access or interact with the
   Software or its functionality over a network, whether paid or unpaid.

   "Non-Commercial Evaluation" means personal, educational, academic research,
   or internal evaluation that is not Production Use, a revenue-generating
   activity, a Hosted Service, work performed for a fee specifically for use or
   evaluation of the Software, or part of a commercial product or service
   offered to a third party.

   "Third-Party Materials" means components identified as being governed by a
   separate license or owned by another party.

